{
  "texts": [
    "After multiplication by sign ϵ (f)(t, A, w) on both sides of (65), and applying the same reasoning as before, one recovers the estimate d dt ∫ R×I |f |(t, A, w)dAdw ≤ 0, in the limit ϵ → 0.",
    "Since the L 1 (R × I) norm of f (t, A, w) does not increase over time and ∥f in ∥ L 1 (R×I) = 0, we conclude that ∥f ∥ L 1 (R×I) = 0 for any t > 0 and thus f 1 (t, A, w) = f 2 (t, A, w) for a.e.",
    "A ∈ R and w ∈ I, and for any t > 0.",
    "□We conclude by providing a sufficient condition which ensures that K[f 1](t, w) = K[f 2](t, w) is satisfied for a.e.",
    "w ∈ I and any t > 0.Lemma 2."
  ]
}